    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I've the same problem, not with instantsearch.js, but on native mobile platforms. But it's a feature that's would be appreciated on all platforms I guess.\n\nI've implemented faceting on e-commerce app, and there is a lot of combinations that's returns 0 products. So I want to disable facets that's returns 0 products to improve UX of this feature.\n\n![filters](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3198863/15958503/4f87d456-2ef6-11e6-8971-c9ebaf6d94e4.png)\n\nFor example if I select filter events, it will return only red and yellow colors. Cool, by keeping the original facets lists, I can easily disable others colors (I mean, they will stay on the screen but with disabled state).\n\nProblem is that theme facets will return only the facets I selected (seems legit). But then it's hard to handle on our side when there is multiple combinations of facets in different categories.\nWould be cool to have an API option to have enabled/disabled state for each facet in the API response.\n",
